\p
\v 19 \w Then|strong="H1768"\w* \w I|strong="H4481"\w* wanted \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w know|strong="H3321"\w* \w what|strong="H1768"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w fourth|strong="H7244"\w* \w beast|strong="H2423"\w* signified—\add the beast\add* \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w was|strong="H1934"\w* \w different|strong="H8133"\w* \w from|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w other|strong="H3605"\w* three, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w beast|strong="H2423"\w* \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w crushed|strong="H1855"\w* \add those that it attacked\add* \w with|strong="H3605"\w* \w its|strong="H3605"\w* \w bronze|strong="H5174"\w* \w claws|strong="H2953"\w*, \w and|strong="H6523"\w* \add then\add* ate \add their flesh\add* \w with|strong="H3605"\w* \w its|strong="H3605"\w* \w iron|strong="H6523"\w* \w teeth|strong="H8128"\w*, \w and|strong="H6523"\w* \w trampled|strong="H7512"\w* \w on|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* parts \w of|strong="H4481"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* bodies \add that it did not eat\add*.  
